  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baa\u0bb8\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Emergency should be withdrawn",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Bar Association of Sri Lanka has urged the recall of the state of emergency declared by Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "This matter has been indicated in the statement issued today (18) with the signatures of the president of the association, President's Attorney Saliya Peiris, and the secretary of the association, Isuru Balapattabendi.",
        "The Sri Lankan Bar Association also stated that freedom of expression including the right to freedom of expression, freedom of speech and freedom of assembly should be upheld.",
        "In addition, it is mentioned in the statement of the association that the basic rights of the public should be ensured and the sovereignty of the people should not be allowed to be violated by the government or its agents."
      ],
